[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":194},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fgithub-download-specific-branch-fix\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fgithub-download-specific-branch-fix\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fgithub-download-specific-branch-fix\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fgithub-download-specific-branch-fix\u002F":169,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fgit\u002F2021\u002F09\u002F24\u002Fgithub-download-specific-branch-fix\u002F":178},"\u002Fgit\u002F20210924\u002F3215116351\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":151,"date":152,"description":153,"extension":154,"lang":155,"meta":156,"navigation":157,"path":158,"readingMinutes":159,"seo":160,"standalone":161,"stem":162,"tags":163,"tldr":166,"updated":166,"url":167,"__hash__":168},"content\u002Fen\u002FGit\u002Fgithub-download-specific-branch-fix.md","Fixing GitHub's Download Button That Won't Respect Branch Selection","6351215321",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":140},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,44,47,55,62,65,71,74,76,82,85,89,92,97,108,112,115,121,131,137],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"Lately when I try to download code from GitHub, the download button keeps ignoring whichever branch I've switched to. Here's how to work around it.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"whats-happening","What's happening",[17,25,26,27,31,32,35,36,39,40,43],{},"GitHub seems to have changed how the Downloads button works. It used to follow whichever branch you'd switched to, but now no matter what branch you're on, the download grabs the default branch (",[28,29,30],"code",{},"Master",", ",[28,33,34],{},"Main","). You can tell by looking at the file name of what gets downloaded — it usually contains the branch name, like ",[28,37,38],{},"xxx-master.zip"," or ",[28,41,42],{},"xxx-main.zip",".",[17,45,46],{},"Here's an example project:",[17,48,49],{},[50,51,52],"a",{"href":52,"rel":53},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhexschool\u002Fweb-layout-training-gulp",[54],"nofollow",[17,56,57,58,61],{},"When I switch to ",[28,59,60],{},"feature\u002Fbs5-fix",", the download should look like this:",[17,63,64],{},"(Check the filename)",[17,66,67],{},[68,69],"img",{"alt":60,"src":70},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FGit\u002F202109240934.png",[17,72,73],{},"But now no matter which branch I switch to, the download always ends up as the default branch:",[17,75,64],{},[17,77,78],{},[68,79],{"alt":80,"src":81},"default branch","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FGit\u002F202109240933.png",[17,83,84],{},"So here are the workarounds.",[12,86,88],{"id":87},"workarounds","Workarounds",[17,90,91],{},"Two simple ways.",[93,94,96],"h3",{"id":95},"use-git-directly","Use Git directly",[17,98,99,100,103,104,107],{},"If you're comfortable with Git, just ",[28,101,102],{},"git clone"," then ",[28,105,106],{},"git checkout [branch]"," to switch to the branch you want. Easiest path.",[93,109,111],{"id":110},"tweak-the-download-url","Tweak the download URL",[17,113,114],{},"If Git isn't your thing, copy the Downloads button URL. For the example above, you'd get:",[17,116,117],{},[50,118,119],{"href":119,"rel":120},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhexschool\u002Fweb-layout-training-gulp\u002Farchive\u002Frefs\u002Fheads\u002Fmaster.zip",[54],[17,122,123,124,126,127,130],{},"If you want to download ",[28,125,60],{},", just swap ",[28,128,129],{},"master"," out:",[17,132,133],{},[50,134,135],{"href":135,"rel":136},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fhexschool\u002Fweb-layout-training-gulp\u002Farchive\u002Frefs\u002Fheads\u002Ffeature\u002Fbs5-fix.zip",[54],[17,138,139],{},"That gets you the specific branch you want.",{"title":141,"searchDepth":142,"depth":142,"links":143},"",2,[144,145,146],{"id":14,"depth":142,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":142,"text":23},{"id":87,"depth":142,"text":88,"children":147},[148